; フリーモード用シナリオ




;■イントロダクション

*introduction_1

; 導入
@wait time=1000
@gameon fade=true time=1000
@playmapsound
@wait time=1000
[texton w=1]
[b][nw]<About Free Mode>[/nw][/b][r]
In Free Mode the player is not bound by the storyline, so you can focus solely on the game.[k]
The scenarios will be minimal and necessary to complete the game, with only a storyline and generic quests aimed at defeating the final boss.[k]
There are also no fixed members for the scenario. There is no specific protagonist either, so you can freely organize your party and proceed with the game. There are also no restrictions on lodging at inns.[k]
In addition, characters such as Max and Riselle, who can't be altered in the story mode, can be freely created here for use in a party.[k]
On the other hand, while it is free, it is also for advanced players, as no specific steps of the strategy are given and there are few necessary hints. It is intended for those who are familiar with this type of game.[k]
In addition, [b]none of the events associated with the story or based on the inn system[/b] occur. If you want to see those, we recommend that you play the story mode.[k]
Let the game begin. First, go to the guild and form a party.[k]
[textoff]
[eventoff]


*introduction_2

; 各種チュートリアル
@wait time=500
@addevent name=戦闘 num=1
@call storage="main01.scn" target=*tutorial_1
[if exp='tf.result']
	[texton w=1]
	There are various [b red]treasure chests, signs, buttons[b] and other items in the dungeon.[/b][k]
	To interact with them, [b red]move to it[b] and either [b red]click[/b] on them, or press the [b red]interact button[b] (by default the space key or the third button on the game pad).[/b][k]
	[textoff]
[endif]
@jump storage="main01.scn" target=*tutorial_3




